article.headline: Columbia 53, Yale 42
article.story: NEW YORK -- Jason Miller had 16 points and 11 rebounds as Columbia rallied for a 53-42 victory over Yale on Friday, ending the Bulldogs' five-game winning streak. Columbia (6-11, 1-2 Ivy League) missed 13 opportunites to take the lead before Patrick Foley's layup with 2:59 to play put the Lions in front 41-39. Foley finished with 12 points, and Noruwa Agho added 10 for Columbia. Garrett Fiddler scored eight points to lead Yale (7-10, 2-1). Columbia held the Bulldogs to 15 points in the second half after trailing 27-18 at halftime. Niko Scott's first basket of the game, a 3-pointer with 9:44 remaining, tied the score at 35. The Lions then closed the game on a 14-3 run -- including eight free throws in the last minute.
